-- Japanese Sold Net 331.9 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2013-04-17T23:53:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-17/japanese-sold-net-331-9-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended April 12 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 331.9 billion yen ($3.4 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 157.7 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 58.6 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 548.2 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 175.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 1569 billion yen in stocks, and sold 265.3 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 1127.9
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
